recalls.Summary: SABERSPORT IS RECALLING 16,270 COMBINATION CORNER AND BUMPER LAMP ASSEMBLIES OF VARIOUS PART NUMBERS SOLD FOR USE AS AFTERMARKET EQUIPMENT FOR VARIOUS PASSENGER VEHICLES.  THESE HEADLAMPS FAIL TO CONFORM TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF FEDERAL MOTOR VEHICLE SAFETY STANDARD NO. 108, "LAMPS, REFLECTIVE DEVICES, AND ASSOCIATED EQUIPMENT."  THESE LAMPS DO NOT CONTAIN THE REQUIRED AMBER SIDE REFLECTORS.
recalls.Consequence: DECREASED LIGHTING VISIBILITY MAY RESULT IN A VEHICLE CRASH.

recalls.Notes: THIS RECALL ONLY PERTAINS TO AFTERMARKET REPLACEMENT EQUIPMENT AND HAS NO RELATION TO ANY ORIGINAL EQUIPMENT INSTALLED ON VEHICLES PRODUCED BY THE VEHICLE MANUFACTURER. THE LIST CAN BE FOUND UNDER "DOCUMENT SEARCH" LOCATED AT THE BOTTOM OF YOUR SCREEN. issues.title: Transmission Synchro Wear
issues.description: The transmission synchros, particularly in 2nd and 3rd gear, wear prematurely causing grinding and difficulty shifting. This is especially common in Type-S models due to aggressive driving and the transmission's design limitations.
issues.fix_description: Transmission rebuild with new synchros, or replacement with rebuilt transmission. Some owners opt for aftermarket synchro sets.
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive shifting, use proper shifting technique, regular transmission fluid changes, let engine warm up before hard driving

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Failure
issues.description: The timing chain tensioner can fail, causing timing chain slack and potentially catastrophic engine damage. The K20A2 engine in the Type-S is particularly susceptible to this issue.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioner, timing chain, and guides. May require additional engine work if damage occurred.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid extended high RPM operation when cold, listen for unusual engine noises

issues.title: Clutch Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The clutch master cylinder develops internal leaks, causing loss of clutch pedal pressure and inability to shift gears. Common failure point in RSX Type-S models.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch master cylinder and slave cylinder, bleed clutch system, replace clutch fluid.
issues.prevention: Regular clutch fluid changes, avoid riding the clutch, proper clutch operation technique

issues.title: Carbon Build-up on Intake Valves
issues.description: The K20A2 engine develops carbon deposits on intake valves over time, reducing performance and fuel economy. More common in higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, throttle body cleaning, intake manifold cleaning.
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, periodic Italian tune-up, regular oil changes, fuel system cleaners

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators fail, causing windows to drop into the door or operate slowly. Both front and rear windows are affected, with driver side being most common.
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator motor and/or regulator assembly, may need window clips.
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing windows when frozen, regular lubrication of window tracks, gentle operation

issues.title: VTEC Solenoid Failure
issues.description: The VTEC solenoid can fail or become clogged, preventing VTEC engagement and reducing high-RPM performance. Screen filter commonly gets clogged with debris.
issues.fix_description: Replace VTEC solenoid and screen filter, clean oil passages, ensure proper oil pressure.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with correct viscosity, avoid cheap oil filters, don't ignore oil pressure warnings

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Cracking
issues.description: The exhaust manifold develops cracks over time due to heat cycling, causing exhaust leaks and potential performance issues. Common on high-mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace exhaust manifold with OEM or aftermarket header, replace manifold gaskets and hardware.
issues.prevention: Allow engine to cool gradually, avoid rapid temperature changes, regular inspection

issues.title: Engine Mount Deterioration
issues.description: Engine mounts, particularly the passenger side mount, deteriorate and fail causing excessive engine movement and vibration. Common in performance-driven vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine mounts with OEM or upgraded aftermarket mounts.
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive driving, gradual acceleration and deceleration, regular inspection

issues.title: A/C Compressor Clutch Failure
issues.description: The A/C compressor clutch fails, causing loss of air conditioning. The clutch bearing and electromagnetic coil commonly fail on these models.
issues.fix_description: Replace A/C compressor clutch assembly, check refrigerant levels, inspect electrical connections.
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance, use A/C periodically during winter, replace cabin air filter

issues.title: CV Joint Wear
issues.description: CV joints wear prematurely, especially in vehicles with performance modifications or aggressive driving. Outer CV joints are more commonly affected.
issues.fix_description: Replace CV joint or entire axle assembly, inspect CV boots for damage.
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, gentle cornering, regular inspection of CV boots, replace torn boots promptly

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: The in-tank fuel pump can fail, causing fuel starvation and potential engine damage. More common in higher mileage vehicles and those driven with low fuel levels.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly, fuel filter, and fuel strainer. May require fuel tank removal.
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Ignition Coil Failure
issues.description: Individual ignition coils fail, causing misfires and reduced performance. The K20A2 engine uses individual coil-on-plug design susceptible to heat-related failures.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed ignition coil(s) and spark plugs, check for carbon tracking on coil boots.
issues.prevention: Regular spark plug replacement, avoid engine modifications that increase heat, use quality ignition components

editorial.tagline: Honda's secret weapon in Acura clothing
editorial.hero_blurb: The RSX Type-S represents the pinnacle of Honda's naturally aspirated performance philosophy wrapped in Acura's premium packaging. This front-wheel-drive rocket delivers an intoxicating blend of high-revving VTEC thrills and everyday usability that defined the golden era of Japanese sport compacts.
editorial.essence: The RSX Type-S is pure Honda engineering excellence disguised as a luxury coupe. Its naturally aspirated K20A2 engine exemplifies the art of high-revving performance, while the chassis offers surgical precision that rewards skilled drivers with an unfiltered connection to the road.
editorial.heritage: Born as the spiritual successor to the beloved Integra Type-R, the RSX Type-S carried Honda's performance DNA into the 21st century. As Acura's flagship sport compact, it bridged the gap between mainstream performance and hardcore track weapons, maintaining the Integra's ethos while adding modern refinement.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers pursued the perfect balance of accessible performance and daily drivability, creating a car that could seamlessly transition from commuter duty to canyon carving. The design emphasized lightweight construction, optimal weight distribution, and aerodynamic efficiency over outright power.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not factory-raced extensively, the RSX Type-S became a grassroots hero in SCCA autocross, NASA time trials, and club racing. Its balanced chassis and bulletproof K-series engine made it a favorite among amateur racers and track day enthusiasts.
editorial.engine_character: The K20A2 is a masterclass in naturally aspirated performance, building power linearly until VTEC engagement at 6000 RPM transforms it into a screaming banshee that pulls hungrily to its 8000 RPM redline. It's an engine that rewards commitment and punishes laziness.
editorial.transmission_feel: The close-ratio 6-speed manual is Honda precision incarnate - short throws, positive engagement, and perfectly spaced ratios that keep the engine in its sweet spot. Each shift feels mechanical and purposeful, connecting driver to drivetrain with surgical precision.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The MacPherson strut front and double wishbone rear suspension creates a platform that's both compliant on rough roads and razor-sharp through corners. The chassis communicates every road surface detail while maintaining composure under aggressive driving.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but still analog in feel, the steering provides excellent road feedback and weights up progressively through corners. It's not as pure as older Honda hydraulic systems but retains enough feel to inspire confidence on twisty roads.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo front calipers and ventilated discs provide strong, fade-resistant stopping power that matches the car's performance capabilities. Pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence during spirited driving sessions.
editorial.sound_signature: A distinctive Honda howl that builds from a purposeful growl at idle to an intoxicating scream at high RPM. The VTEC crossover produces an unmistakable metallic wail that's music to enthusiast ears, especially with an aftermarket exhaust.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who appreciate naturally aspirated engines, Honda reliability, and precise handling dynamics. Perfect for enthusiasts who want genuine performance without exotic car maintenance costs or complexity.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking low-end torque, luxury amenities, or effortless highway cruising. The high-strung nature requires commitment to extract performance, and rear seat space is minimal.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with maintenance records showing regular oil changes and VTEC-friendly driving habits. Avoid heavily modified cars unless documentation proves quality work, and budget for potential clutch replacement on higher-mileage examples.
